# PROJECT SCOPE

I want to design a demo user agent for our new Architecture, called modular banking. The goal of the application is to show the business functionality to the business users of the bank we are selling to. At the same time we want to show to the technical users of the bank the underlying architecture. The goal of the demonstration is to show to the business users that the functionality/user experience remains the same - however the underlying technology architecture is changing a lot: From a monolith that was used before, it now focuses on smaller services performing a specific task. 

My demo user agent needs to have the following tabs:
1. A "mobile app" tab with standard smartphone resolution. For the demo, just create a standard html tab and make it look like mobile. The mobile app is what the bank's customer will be using. 
2. A "branch application" tab with a user interface for the bank's employee. From this user interface, the bank employee will be performing actions on behalf of the bank or the user, on top of the customer's data.
3. A "headless tab". In this tab, I need to have two things: On the top I need a feature to call REST APIs. I need to see the REST API URI, select the REST API method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE is enough). Then i need a box on the left to put the payload (for POST etc.) and a box on the right to see the response. All my APIs will use JSON request/response, so optimize for that. On the bottom i need a feature to view events emitted by the platform. The events are coming from an Apache Kafka middleware or Azure event hub. The "headless tab" needs to be populated with data when i perform an operation in one of the first two tabs. For example, when i view a list of my transactions for a current account in the mobile app, I want to show on the headless tab the respective GET API with the account ID in the URI and then in the response tab to see the JSON response returned from the actual API. 
4. An "architecture tab". Here i will draw the system's architecture. I will provide a PUML file later to do this dynamically. I will also provide a mapping file with PUML classes and API endpoints. I want to make the PUML visualizer dynamically show with a different color the component i am using for the current operation. For example, when i view a list of my transactions, this will be retrieved by a Microservice called Holdings. When i view the list of transactions from tabs 1 or 2, i want the PUML visualization to change the color of Holdings. For PUML visualization, use the /Users/gpanagiotopoulos/ModularDemo/PUML/plantuml-mit-1.2025.1.jar provided. 
5. An "assistant tab". Here i will create a RAG model to provide answers to the user on how the architecture works. I will supply the documentation later.


# TECHNOLOGY STACK

The application needs to use html/css/js front end with Python Flask back-end. Refer to best practices section for details. Stick to the best practices whenever possible.

